<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910215-0150</DOCNO><DOCID>910215-0150.</DOCID><HL>   Ex-Owner of Thrift   In California Indicted   By U.S. Grand Jury</HL><DATE>02/15/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4</SO><IN>SAVINGS AND LOANS, THRIFTS, CREDIT UNIONS (SAL)</IN><GV>JUSTICE DEPARTMENT (JUS)</GV><LP>   LOS ANGELES -- A federal grand jury returned a 31-countindictment against Robert Allan Ferrante, former owner ofConsolidated Savings Bank, and eight others in connectionwith the 1986 failure of the Orange County, Calif., savingsand loan.   The thrift's failure is estimated to have cost taxpayersmore than $30 million, said U.S. Attorney General DickThornburgh.</LP><TEXT>   Mr. Ferrante, 41 years old, of Newport Beach, who was oncechairman of the thrift, couldn't be reached for comment.   Mr. Ferrante and the others were charged with wire fraud,mail fraud, fraudulent participation in loan proceeds, falseentries, bank fraud and false statements. According toSpecial U.S. Attorney Gregory D. Schetina and Assistant U.S.Attorney Maurice A. Leiter, the charges center on two allegedmassive fraud schemes perpetrated in 1985 and 1986.   In one purported scheme, several defendants allegedlyconspired to evade federal regulations limiting the amount ofmoney that could be loaned to any one borrower and to evadeprohibitions against loans to affiliates of Consolidated.   In the other alleged scheme, several defendants werecharged with attempting to funnel Consolidated's money intoan Anaheim fireworks company controlled by Mr. Ferrante.   Other former Consolidated officials indicted are OttavioAntonio Angotti, 54, of La Habra, a former chief executiveofficer; Ronald Lee Bartholomew, 59, of Corona Del Mar, aformer Consolidated attorney; Raymond Lloyd Arthun, 42, ofTustin, a former officer and director; and Eric Chess Bronk,44, of Corona Del Mar, a former attorney and consultant.   Also charged were Peter Antonio Sardagna, 47, of LagunaHills; William Edgar Crowder, 42, of Covina; Sigmund Kohnen,43, of Las Vegas, Nev.; and James Charles Allee, 36, ofLaguna Beach. None could be reached for comment.</TEXT></DOC>